I have been scoping out that very particular valley for several days now.<br>
I have also consulted several other players in area on how to get through that valley.<br>
Couple of items to note on that valley (which I affectionately refer to as the Stone-Lord's valley).<br>
<br>
1. That valley for all practical purpose the shortest (not necessarily the best) route to the dragon (good).<br>
2. Valley is very-very-very narrow (bad).<br>
3. Valley is very-very-very short (good).<br>
4. Spawn rate is very fast (bad)<br>
5. Aggro range is huge (I think that this is good, since valley is narrow and short anyway it can be used to our advantage)<br>
6. The valley has 4 (possibly 5 layers of MOBs aggression). 1st are the 3 harvesters, then there are at least 3 layers of 2-3 Stone lords that are (I believe) all linked (all-bad).<br>
<br>
Although a large multi-group formation, with 40+ should be able to punch through with brute force, I am weary of the fact that there is an Outlooker tower right on the other side.<br>
The tower usually means more MOBs right in the vicinity.<br>
<br>
I do not have at this time a tactical method to efficiently go through that specific valley.<br>
<br>
None the less, as short as the trip was =), I still had fun.<br>
<br>
BTW... suggestion...<br>
If a TPW seems imminent, retreat...<br>
Caster run out of spawn zones,<br>
while tanks attempt to maintain aggro and die as close as possible to a rez safe area.<br>
